tion of pastoral to epic.Drawing on the commentary tradition and engaging with current critical debates, this study of Spenser's interpretation, imitation and revision of Virgil casts new light on both poets-and on the genre of pastoral itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPastoral poetry, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 4aShakespeare 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aColin Clouts Come Home Againe.  aEclogues.  aEdmund Spenser.  aRenaissance.  aServius.  aThe Shepheardes Calender.  aVirgilian career.  apastoral poetry.  apoetic programme.  athe English Virgil.1 aPugh, Syrithe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610388840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526103888423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526103888/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles